
All examples require that BAT was successfully installed in the system.
Instructions on how to run the examples are either inside the source
code (for ROOT macros) or in the README file (for compiled examples)

You can also find tutorials on BAT webpage: www.mppmu.mpg.de/bat

Examples in this directory:
-------------------------------

fastfitter:
   Examples showing the most basic usage of BAT for fitting data
   using ROOT TF1 function.
   (ROOT macros)

simplecompiled:
   Example showing how to define own complicated models and build
   a program for running with BAT. It shows fits using two functions
   when assuming asymmetric uncertainties.
   (Compiled program)

roointerface:
   Examples of usage of the RooInterface showing how BAT analysis can be
   performed on a RooFit workspace.

templatefitter:
   Examples for how to fit several templates to a data set using
   1-dim. histograms. The examples feature the BCTemplateFitter which
   is included in the models directory. 
   (ROOT macros and compiled programs)
